1. Use SafeArea Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The SafeArea widget in Flutter ensures that the UI of the app is displayed within the safe boundaries of the device.
It avoids overlapping with system UI elements like:

Status bar
Notch
Navigation bar

This helps in making the app responsive and properly visible on all devices.

// main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: SafeAreaExample(),
    );
  }
}

class SafeAreaExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("SafeArea Example"),
      ),
      body: SafeArea(
        child: Container(
          color: Colors.blue,
          child: Center(
            child: Text(
              "This is inside SafeArea",
              style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 20),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}